    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold pb-1">Introduction</h2>
    <p class="pb-4">Welcome to Happ - the exclusive event platform designed with your privacy in mind. We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect from you, how we use it, the lawful basis of it, and how we uphold your rights in respect to this information. By using our app, you are agreeing to our <a href="https://www.happ.rsvp/legal/terms-of-use" target="_blank" class="text-blue-700">Terms of Use</a> and the terms outlined in this policy. Please read carefully.</p>
  
    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold pb-1">Information We Collect and How We Use It</h2>
    <p class="pb-4">
      When you sign in to Happ using third-party services, such as Google and Apple, your authentication is managed through Firebase, a development platform owned by Google. We collect and store your name, email address, profile picture (if provided, otherwise one is assigned by us), and a unique identifier provided by Firebase. This information, along with an additional unique user identifier assigned by Happ for user identification within our systems, and an automatically assigned username, are securely stored on our servers. Additionally, with your consent, we collect and store a device identifier for the purpose of sending push notifications. You can learn more about how Firebase uses your information in <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank" class="text-blue-700">Firebase's Privacy Policy</a>. The lawful basis for this processing is the performance of the contract between you and Happ, as it is necessary for us to provide you the services you have signed up for.<br><br>
      Happ allows you to create and manage exclusive, invitation-only events. For this purpose, we collect and store event-related details such as the event name, pictures, description, location, address, date, time, and the user relationships to the event (guests, hosts, creator, and invited but not confirmed users). This information is used to provide event details to guests and hosts, differentiate between guests and hosts, and facilitate event management. The lawful basis for this processing is our legitimate interest in providing a comprehensive and effective event management platform.<br><br>
      When you accept an invitation to an event as a guest, you will receive a "Pass" containing the event name, your name, username, profile picture, and a unique QR code. This pass primarily serves as a means of verification at the event, ensuring that you have been legitimately invited. The processing of this data is justified by our legitimate interest in ensuring the security and proper execution of events.<br><br>
      The QR code on your pass is unique and encrypted, adding a layer of security to your data. Event hosts can scan this QR code to verify your attendance, but they are not able to decrypt it or access any additional information from it.<br><br>
      With your explicit consent, we may collect your location data. This data is not saved on our servers unless the event's location data is your location and it is used to facilitate finding a location for an event. Additionally, when you choose to upload photos as part of the event details, we collect and store these images. The legal basis for this data collection is your consent.<br><br>
      Our "Friendship" feature allows you to establish relationships with other users on the platform. No additional personal data is collected through this feature beyond what is already outlined in this policy. The visibility of your existing personal data, such as your name, username, and profile picture, is standard across our platform and is visible to all users.<br><br>
      Happ sends push notifications to keep you updated about various activities, including receiving an invitation, leaving a confirmed event, an event's cancellation, friend requests, updates to event details, acceptance of your invitations, and event reminders. These notifications are facilitated by a device identifier, which we collect and store with your consent of receiving notifications. These notifications are sent based on our legitimate interest in keeping you informed about your activities and updates on Happ.
    </p>

