    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold pb-1">Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
    <p class="pb-4">
      We retain your data for as long as necessary until you delete your account. Upon account deletion, all of your data is permanently deleted from our servers. This includes data directly associated with your user account such as your name, username, email address, profile picture, and unique identifiers.<br><br>
      However, please note that the deletion of the relationship between your account and any event, as well as the deletion of your device identifier, may be slightly delayed depending on the server's workload.<br><br>
      If you are the creator of an event and delete your account, the creator status will pass to another host if one exists. If there are no other hosts for the event, the event will be automatically cancelled and all information related to that event, including user relationships with the event (guests, hosts, creator, and invited but not confirmed users), will be deleted.<br><br>
      Additionally, when an event is deleted or 7 days after the event date has passed, all event information, including user relationships with the event (guests, hosts, creator, and invited but not confirmed users), is also permanently deleted.<br><br>
      Please be aware that these deletion processes are irreversible, and we do not maintain backups of user data after account deletion.
